Tmux
====
tmux is a terminal multiplexer

What is a terminal multiplexer? It lets you switch easily between several programs in one terminal, detach them (they keep running in the background) and reattach them to a different terminal. And do a lot more.




start Tmux: Type "tmux" in terminal

Command key
===========
By default, you can enter in the command mode by typing Ctrl+b, then you can do all the things that follow


Pannels
=======
Split pannels into left and right: %

Split pannels into up and down: "

Move through pannels: Ctrl+b and then use key arrows

Make pannel fullscreen: z

Shrink pannel back to previous size: z

Closing pannels: Ctrl+d


Windows
=======
New window: c

Switch to previous window: p

Switch to next windows: n

Rename current windows: ,

Switch to window number x: Ctrl+b and then type number x


Sessions
========
Create a session when starting tmux: tmux new -s name_of_session

Detach current session: d

List of tmux running sessions: tmux ls

Connect to tmux session: tmux attach -t 0

Rename session: tmux rename-session -t 0 new_name

==============================================================
Exit this manual -> Press "Esc" -> Type ":q!" -> press "Enter"
==============================================================
